This is highly unverified, but I pulled it from a post on caster's realm:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> General Notes:<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Dwarch is serving as War Leader; Zathrax is serving as Scout Master<br>
2. The first battle will be faught during &quot;The Festival&quot; (8 days after Bertoxx is summoned to NK)<br>
3. The war will be faught over a long period of time (weeks perhaps), and will involve several fronts.<br>
4. All &quot;good&quot; cities on Antonica will be involved (Qeynos, Halas, Rivervale, Freeport, Kaladim, Felwithe/Kelethin, Ak'anon)<br>
5. Many Gods will be involved, including Rallos Zek, Tunare, Bertox, Innoruuk, and others.<br>
6. Zones will behave differently. Be VERY cautious what spells you may rely upon.<br>
7. Mobs that are normally level-restricted (Vox, Naggy) will not be for this event.<br>
8. There is a strong chance that both bridges and boats will be down for portions of the war.<br>
9. The safety zones will be Surefall Glade, Arena, Lower Kaladim, and Velious.<br>
10. Bertox will have an army of &quot;planar beings.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Planes of Karana<br>
<br>
1. Bertox will be summoned to NK<br>
2. Gate and teleportation spells will either (a) not work or (b) have a HIGH failure/fizzle rate. I'd be willing to bet this is spells cast IN The zones, not spells teleporting you TO the zones.<br>
3. Ressurection will only be possible within these zones via res stick<br>
<br>
Qeynos<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Generals for the defense of Qeynos include Shakar and Wamsutta.<br>
2. Trakanon and Bertox himself will be assaulting the city.<br>
3. Bertox will assault the city after the &quot;Festival&quot; mentioned above.<br>
4. Antonious Bayle will lead an army to confront Bertox in WK.<br>
5. Kane Bayle will show up with half the bloodsabre army in an effort to kill Antonious.<br>
6. If Kane and his army are killed, it will be discovered he in a imposter and the real Kane will appear in Qeynos along with enough Bloodsabres to take the city over.<br>
7. Blackburrow Gnolls will aid Bertox.<br>
8. Bertox is un-killable until he hits Qeynos Hills.<br>
<br>
Halas<br>
<br>
1. Expect a visit from Lady Vox.<br>
2. The Tribunal will close Halas during the war (what this means I dunnoe)<br>
<br>
Rivervale<br>
<br>
1. Expect a visit from Lord Nagafen.<br>
2. An undead army from Kithicor will assault Rivervale when Innoruuk appears in Freeport.<br>
3. The assault can only be stopped by killing the necromancers in Kithicor who are raising the zombies.<br>
4. Legion of the Little Folk will be defending.<br>
<br>
Freeport<br>
<br>
1. A Teir'dal army will be assaulting the city from Nektulos.<br>
2. Innoruuk will attack the city armed with Lanys' Guardian Staff (more info?), a Dark Elf army, and the Militia will join him.<br>
3. Expect a visit from Lord Nagafen if he is not routed in Rivervale.<br>
<br>
Kaladim<br>
<br>
1. Lower Kaladim will be a safe zone.<br>
2. Will be assaulted by a level 15-30 Dark Elf army (with a few 50s thrown in)<br>
<br>
Kelethin/Felwithe/GFay<br>
<br>
1. The Ring of Scale will aid in defending this area. If you do NOT have good Ring faction, it is suggested you get your butt into Mistmore NOW or avoid this area during the war.<br>
2. Claws of Veeshan will be assaulting this area (wyverns and drakes from CS, level 40-52). EVERYONE will be KOS to Claws in Gfay, regardless of your usual faction reading.<br>
3. Orcs (level 10-50) will be assaulting from Crushbone<br>
<br>
Cabilis<br>
<br>
1. The Combine Empire will re-awaken and try to level Cabilis <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
